Rudradevasaṃskārita Dattanāma Mahāvihāra, Dattanāma Mahāvihāra

There are three (competing) explanations as to the monastery's name:

(1) Bhāṣkaradeva Varma and Rudradeva Varma, two brothers who came from Gauḍa, established Hiraṇyavarṇa Mahāvihāra and Dattanāma Mahāvihāra respectively. Rudradeva organized the samyak five times and managed the donations so as to established this monastery. The vihāra is therefore named Datta (Vajrācārya NS 1121, 83).

(2) There was once a pond in front of the Dau Bāhāḥ. The name dau is derived from the word daha which means pond (ibid.).

(3) King Aśoka Malla (father of Jayasthiti Malla) had two queens. This bāhāḥ was made for these two queens, and was named Dvau Bāhāla: the modern name dau is derived from dvau (Vajrācārya VS 2058, 48).
